  "intent_precise": "78d33c-part-3.ot2.apiv2: Using Reagents (labware, slot 2), Reservoir (reservoir, slot 5), plate4deg (labware, slot Plate at 4 Degrees C), mag_plate (labware, slot Mag Plate). With temperature module, magnetic module. (1) Pause: Please Refill the 300 uL Tip Box\n                     and Empty the Tip Waste (2) Pause: format (3) Pause: Paused (4) Set temperature to temp_mod_setting\u00b0C. (5) Disengage magnets to release beads. (6) Transfer 60\u00b5L from source A1 to column 0. (7) Transfer 200\u00b5L from source to destination. (8) Wait 1 seconds. (9) Transfer 140\u00b5L from source to destination. (10) Incubate for 10 minutes. (11) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (12) Pause for incubation. (13) Transfer 180\u00b5L from source to destination. (14) Wait 1 seconds. (15) Transfer 50\u00b5L from source to destination. (16) Wait 1 seconds. (17) Wait 0 seconds. (18) Wait 30 seconds. (19) Wait 0 seconds. (20) Disengage magnets to release beads. (21) Pause for incubation. (22) Transfer 16\u00b5L from source (multiple wells) to destination (multiple wells). (23) Wait 1 seconds. (24) Pause: Cover, vortex, spin, incubate,\n        uncover and return the plate. Resume (25) Incubate for 2 minutes. (26) Engage magnets at height_engagemm height for bead separation. (27) Pause for incubation. (28) Pause: Place a fresh 200 uL PCR plate on the temperature module.\n     Place index plate on the reagents block. Resume. (29) Transfer 15\u00b5L from source (A1, A1) to column (0, A1). (30) Wait 1 seconds. (31) Transfer 40\u00b5L from source to destination. (32) Pause: Continue to DNA-POST-PCR-1 Purification Post Indexing protocol.",
  "intent_concise": "Perform magnetic bead separation, temperature control (temp_mod_setting\u00b0C). (volumes 10\u00b5L-250\u00b5L, ~14 min total)",
  "intent": "Here's the third part of protocol 78d33c for the OT-2, where you'll be working with reagents in slot 2, reservoir in slot 5, the 4\u00b0C plate, and the magnetic plate using both temperature and magnetic modules. Start by refilling the 300 \u00b5L tip box and emptying tip waste, then set the temperature module to temp_mod_setting\u00b0C and disengage the magnets before transferring 60\u00b5L from A1 to column 0, followed by 200\u00b5L and 140\u00b5L transfers with brief waits between each step. After a 10-minute incubation, engage the magnets at height_engagemm for bead separation, then proceed with 180\u00b5L and 50\u00b5L transfers with various wait times (including a 30-second wait), followed by disengaging magnets and transferring 16\u00b5L to multiple wells. Complete the protocol with a 2-minute incubation after covering/vortexing/spinning the plate, re-engage magnets, place fresh plates as prompted, and finish with 15\u00b5L transfers from A1 to column 0/A1 and a final 40\u00b5L transfer before moving to the DNA-POST-PCR-1 purification protocol.",
